    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-10-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-10-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="58"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d58">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Goschen</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 59.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">New London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-10-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 14, 1894</hi>
                        </date>. (Received October 16.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I duly informed Her Majesty’s principal secretary
                    of state for foreign affairs of the reply of the United States Government
                    respecting the proposed intervention between China and Japan, which you <pb
                        facs="0077" n="71" xml:id="pg_71"/> were good enough to communicate to me by
                    telegraph on the 12th instant.</p>
                <p>I am now instructed by his lordship to call your attention to the fact that the
                    intervention contemplated would be limited to diplomatic action and would only
                    take place in the event of a suitable opportunity presenting itself for the
                    adoption of such a course.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. E. Goschen.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
